President Samia Suluhu Hassan has expressed her deep regret on the passing of the World Health Organisation's director of the Department of Neglected Tropical Diseases (NTDs), Dr Mwele Malecela. Dr Mwele passed away in Geneva yesterday. After news of the passing of renowned Tanzanian medical scientist went viral on various social media platform on Thursday, President Samia who in France for official visit twitted: “I have been saddened by the death of Dr @mwelentuli [Mwelecela Malecela], truly African who worked diligently in Tanzania and beyond,” President Samia twitted through her verified twitter handle @Suluhusamia She used the platform to extend her message of condolence to the family of former Prime Minister John Malecela, over the loss of her daughter as she concluded by saying: “May God rest her soul in eternal peace. Amen.” Mwele, former Tanzania’s National Institute for Medical Research (NIMR) director, announced in 2019 that she was diagnosed with cancer. In November, 2017, the renowned medical scientist scooped the 2017 Kyelem Prize in recognition of her efforts in controlling neglected tropical diseases (NTDs).